ringswitchBasePSFanSpeed.name: ringswitchBasePSFanSpeed
ringswitchBasePSFanSpeed.description: The number of revolutions per minute being reported by the fan internal to the system power supply. If this value is read as zero, the fan is no longer operating

ringswitchBaseExtFanSpeed.name: ringswitchBaseExtFanSpeed
ringswitchBaseExtFanSpeed.description: The number of revolutions per minute being reported by the external system fan. If this value is read as zero, the fan is no longer operating

ringswitchBaseRipSapSuppression.name: ringswitchBaseRipSapSuppression
ringswitchBaseRipSapSuppression.description: If this variable is set to enable the system will only forward broadcast-addressed IPX RIP and SAP Response frames to those ports that have recently sourced such a frame. This reduces the number of gratuitous frames sent out on LANs that only have IPX workstations attached. A value of disable causes no special action to be taken for such frames.

ringswitchBaseAREConversion.name: ringswitchBaseAREConversion
ringswitchBaseAREConversion.description: This variable controls the action taken when forwarding All Routes Explorer frames. enable-first: convert all ARE frames with a RIF length of 2 to STE frames. enable-all: convert all ARE frames to STE frames. enable-bcast-first: convert all ARE frames with the broadcast destination address, with a RIF length of 2 to STE frames. enable-bcast-all: convert all ARE frames with the broadcast destination address to STE frames. disable: follow normal forwarding rules for ARE frames.

ringswitchBaseStpMode.name: ringswitchBaseStpMode
ringswitchBaseStpMode.description: This selects the mode of operation of the spanning tree protocol. When set to ibm-sr, spanning tree protocol BPDUs are sent to the 802.5 LBS functional address on all interface types, and TCN BPDUs are not generated. When set to ieee8021d, TCN BPDUs are generated, and the IEEE 802.1D group address (01 80 C2 00 00 00 in canonical form) is used as the destination address for BPDUs on interfaces of types other than 802.5

ringswitchBaseRMONState.name: ringswitchBaseRMONState
ringswitchBaseRMONState.description: Setting this to 'enable' activates the RMON probe function in the Ringswitch. When RMON has been enabled it is configured according to ringswitchBaseRMONMirrorPort, ringswitchPortRMONMode and ringswitchPortRMONSnoop mib entries. Setting it to 'disable' de-activates the RMON probe function. When RMON is disabled, all other RMON related mib entries defined by the Madge Ringwitch MIB will be ignored (but their values will still be settable). ringswitchBaseRMONState defaults to 'disable'.

ringswitchBaseBackPlaneType.name: ringswitchBaseBackPlaneType
ringswitchBaseBackPlaneType.description: This variable reports the type of chassis that the Ringswitch is mounted in.

ringswitchBaseRMONMirrorPort.name: ringswitchBaseRMONMirrorPort
ringswitchBaseRMONMirrorPort.description: This variable controls the RMON mirroring facility. A value of 0 means mirroring is disabled. Mirroring is enabled by setting this variable to the ifNumber of the port to which mirroring will apply and by setting ringswitchBaseRMONState to 'enable'. When mirroring is enabled, the Ringswitch sends all RMON related traffic to the mirror port (except for MAC frames).

ringswitchBaseTotalResetCounters.name: ringswitchBaseTotalResetCounters
ringswitchBaseTotalResetCounters.description: Use this variable to reset all the counters on the Ringswitch, including those in the ringswitchGenPort, dot1dSRPort, ifEntry and fddimib groups.

ringswitchBaseDownloadMode.name: ringswitchBaseDownloadMode
ringswitchBaseDownloadMode.description: Use this variable to select the mode for all subsequent download operations. normal - device will enter the loader prior to downloading. active - device will NOT enter the loader and perform the download online.

ringswitchPortTable.name: ringswitchPortTable
ringswitchPortTable.description: A table that contains general port information.

ringswitchPortNum.name: ringswitchPortNum
ringswitchPortNum.description: The port number of the port for which this entry contains Ringswitch management information.

ringswitchPortRingStatus.name: ringswitchPortRingStatus
ringswitchPortRingStatus.description: The status of the ring to which this port is connected. normal: Inserted into Classic ring single: Single Station beaconing: Beaconing Detected normal-fdx: DTR link in full duplex (TXI) mode dtr-wait: DTR Concentrator port waiting for attached station to insert

ringswitchPortAdapterStatus.name: ringswitchPortAdapterStatus
ringswitchPortAdapterStatus.description: The status of the adapter used by this port.

ringswitchPortIfMode.name: ringswitchPortIfMode
ringswitchPortIfMode.description: Node or concentrator status of the port.

ringswitchPortRingSpeed.name: ringswitchPortRingSpeed
ringswitchPortRingSpeed.description: Speed of the ring to which this port is connected.

ringswitchPortTestState.name: ringswitchPortTestState
ringswitchPortTestState.description: Current state of the bridge test.

ringswitchPortTestPhase.name: ringswitchPortTestPhase
ringswitchPortTestPhase.description: Current phase of the bridge test.

ringswitchPortSummary.name: ringswitchPortSummary
ringswitchPortSummary.description: This is a four octet field which packs some of the port attributes into a single mib entry. Each nibble represents a different attribute of the port: ifAdminStatus (most significant), ringswitchPortRingStatus, ringswitchPortAdapterStatus, ringswitchPortMediaType, ringswitchPortIfMode, ringswitchPortRingSpeed, ringswitchPortTestState, ringswitchPortTestError (least significant)

ringswitchPortAddress.name: ringswitchPortAddress
ringswitchPortAddress.description: The hard wired address of the port.

ringswitchPortLAA.name: ringswitchPortLAA
ringswitchPortLAA.description: The locally administered address of the port.

ringswitchPortStationType.name: ringswitchPortStationType
ringswitchPortStationType.description: Workstations-only status of the port; if this is limited, the port only has workstations on it, and broadcast frames received on this port will not be transmitted on other limited ports.

ringswitchPortRPSEnable.name: ringswitchPortRPSEnable
ringswitchPortRPSEnable.description: Enables or disables the Ring Parameter Server function on the port. If this variable is set to enabled, the port will enable the RPS functional address, and respond to Request Parameters MAC frames, supplying the port's segment number in the response.

ringswitchPortCutThruEnable.name: ringswitchPortCutThruEnable
ringswitchPortCutThruEnable.description: Enables or disables cut-through switching on the port. In some circumstances (e.g., 4 to 16 MB switching), cut-through will always be disabled, irrespective of the state of this variable.

ringswitchPortInOctets.name: ringswitchPortInOctets
ringswitchPortInOctets.description: 48 bit version of the interface MIB counter ifInOctets.

ringswitchPortOutOctets.name: ringswitchPortOutOctets
ringswitchPortOutOctets.description: 48 bit version of the interface MIB counter ifOutOctets.

ringswitchPortSpecInFrames.name: ringswitchPortSpecInFrames
ringswitchPortSpecInFrames.description: 48 bit version of the Bridge MIB counter srPortSpecInFrames.

ringswitchPortSpecOutFrames.name: ringswitchPortSpecOutFrames
ringswitchPortSpecOutFrames.description: 48 bit version of the Bridge MIB counter srPortSpecOutFrames.

ringswitchPortApeInFrames.name: ringswitchPortApeInFrames
ringswitchPortApeInFrames.description: 48 bit version of the Bridge MIB counter srPortApeInFrames.

ringswitchPortApeOutFrames.name: ringswitchPortApeOutFrames
ringswitchPortApeOutFrames.description: 48 bit version of the Bridge MIB counter srPortApeOutFrames.

ringswitchPortSteInFrames.name: ringswitchPortSteInFrames
ringswitchPortSteInFrames.description: 48 bit version of the Bridge MIB counter srPortSteInFrames.

ringswitchPortSteOutFrames.name: ringswitchPortSteOutFrames
ringswitchPortSteOutFrames.description: 48 bit version of the Bridge MIB counter srPortSteOutFrames.

ringswitchPortResetCounters.name: ringswitchPortResetCounters
ringswitchPortResetCounters.description: Use this variable to reset all the counters on this port, including those in the ringswitchPort, dot1dSRPort, ifEntry and fddimib groups.

ringswitchPortFixupMode.name: ringswitchPortFixupMode
ringswitchPortFixupMode.description: This MIB variable controls operation of protocol fixups on an FDDI linecard. When set to fddi-all, embedded MAC addresses in frames are bit-reversed to convert the frames into native FDDI format

ringswitchPortForwardMode.name: ringswitchPortForwardMode
ringswitchPortForwardMode.description: This MIB variable controls the bridging modes that are enabled on this port. Any combination of the two types of bridging - transparent and source routing can be enabled/disabled.

ringswitchPortRMONCapabilities.name: ringswitchPortRMONCapabilities
ringswitchPortRMONCapabilities.description: A value that indicates the RMON capabilities of the port. The value represents the highest level RMON mode which the port can support. 'disabled' is the lowest level and indicates no RMON capabilities 'snooping' is the highest level and indicates that the port is capable of running in all RMON modes

ringswitchPortRMONMode.name: ringswitchPortRMONMode
ringswitchPortRMONMode.description: Controls the types of frames passed to the RMON probe function for processing as follows: disabled - no frames passed to the RMON probe economy - MAC frames required for token ring specific groups as follows: MLStats table Token Ring Ring station table standard - all frames snooping - all frames provided by the 'economy' mode plus any frames originating from or destined for the 'snoop address' controlled by ringswitchPortRMONSnoop

ringswitchPortRMONSnoop.name: ringswitchPortRMONSnoop
ringswitchPortRMONSnoop.description: This controls the RMON snoop address used when ringswitchPortRMONMode is set to 'snooping'. A value of all zeroes results in no snooping taking place.

ringswitchPortTransparentInFrames.name: ringswitchPortTransparentInFrames
ringswitchPortTransparentInFrames.description: 48 bit version of the Bridge MIB counter TpPortInFrames.

ringswitchPortTransparentOutFrames.name: ringswitchPortTransparentOutFrames
ringswitchPortTransparentOutFrames.description: 48 bit version of the Bridge MIB counter TpPortOutFrames.

ringswitchPortTransparentDiscFrames.name: ringswitchPortTransparentDiscFrames
ringswitchPortTransparentDiscFrames.description: 48 bit version of the Bridge MIB counter TpPortInDiscards.

ringswitchPortLEDs.name: ringswitchPortLEDs
ringswitchPortLEDs.description: An octet string containing the colour of every LED on the port, one per octet: off (1), on-red (2), on-green (3), on-yellow (4), flash-red (5), flash-green (6), flash-yellow (7), flash-blue (8), flash-green-anti-phase (9), flash-yellow-anti-phase (10)

ringswitchFwdAdminState.name: ringswitchFwdAdminState
ringswitchFwdAdminState.description: The desired state of the switches forwarding modes. This allows source routing and/or transparent bridging to be enabled/disabled for the whole Ringswitch

ringswitchFwdOperState.name: ringswitchFwdOperState
ringswitchFwdOperState.description: The actual state of switches forwarding modes. If for some reason the switch is unable operate in the mode requested then the operating state may differ from the AdminState.

ringswitchFwdPortTable.name: ringswitchFwdPortTable
ringswitchFwdPortTable.description: A table that contains forwarding information about every port that is associated with this Ringswitch. Transparent, source-route, srt and srt plus ports are included.

ringswitchFwdPortEntry.name: ringswitchFwdPortEntry
ringswitchFwdPortEntry.description: A list of forwarding information for each port of the Ringswitch.

ringswitchFwdPort.name: ringswitchFwdPort
ringswitchFwdPort.description: The port number of the port for which this entry contains forwarding information. This value is the same as the value of dot1dBasePort for the equivalent port.

ringswitchFwdPortMode.name: ringswitchFwdPortMode
ringswitchFwdPortMode.description: This MIB variable controls the bridging modes that are enabled on this port. Any combination of the two types of bridging - transparent and source routing can be enabled/disabled.

ringswitchFwdPortStationType.name: ringswitchFwdPortStationType
ringswitchFwdPortStationType.description: Workstations-only status of the port; if this is limited, the port only has workstations on it, and broadcast frames received on this port will not be transmitted on other limited ports.

ringswitchFwdPortCutThruEnable.name: ringswitchFwdPortCutThruEnable
ringswitchFwdPortCutThruEnable.description: Enables or disables cut-through switching on the port. In some circumstances (e.g., 4 to 16 MB switching), cut-through will always be disabled, irrespective of the state of this variable.

ringswitchFwdPortSpecInFrames.name: ringswitchFwdPortSpecInFrames
ringswitchFwdPortSpecInFrames.description: 48 bit version of the Bridge MIB counter srPortSpecInFrames.

ringswitchFwdPortSpecOutFrames.name: ringswitchFwdPortSpecOutFrames
ringswitchFwdPortSpecOutFrames.description: 48 bit version of the Bridge MIB counter srPortSpecOutFrames.

ringswitchFwdPortApeInFrames.name: ringswitchFwdPortApeInFrames
ringswitchFwdPortApeInFrames.description: 48 bit version of the Bridge MIB counter srPortApeInFrames.

ringswitchFwdPortApeOutFrames.name: ringswitchFwdPortApeOutFrames
ringswitchFwdPortApeOutFrames.description: 48 bit version of the Bridge MIB counter srPortApeOutFrames.

ringswitchFwdPortSteInFrames.name: ringswitchFwdPortSteInFrames
ringswitchFwdPortSteInFrames.description: 48 bit version of the Bridge MIB counter srPortSteInFrames.

ringswitchFwdPortSteOutFrames.name: ringswitchFwdPortSteOutFrames
ringswitchFwdPortSteOutFrames.description: 48 bit version of the Bridge MIB counter srPortSteOutFrames.

ringswitchFwdPortTransparentInFrames.name: ringswitchFwdPortTransparentInFrames
ringswitchFwdPortTransparentInFrames.description: 48 bit version of the Bridge MIB counter TpPortInFrames.

ringswitchFwdPortTransparentOutFrames.name: ringswitchFwdPortTransparentOutFrames
ringswitchFwdPortTransparentOutFrames.description: 48 bit version of the Bridge MIB counter TpPortOutFrames.

ringswitchFwdPortTransparentDiscFrames.name: ringswitchFwdPortTransparentDiscFrames
ringswitchFwdPortTransparentDiscFrames.description: 48 bit version of the Bridge MIB counter TpPortInDiscards.

ringswitchFwdPortTestState.name: ringswitchFwdPortTestState
ringswitchFwdPortTestState.description: Current state of the bridge test.

ringswitchFwdPortTestPhase.name: ringswitchFwdPortTestPhase
ringswitchFwdPortTestPhase.description: Current phase of the bridge test.

ringswitchFwdPortTbForce.name: ringswitchFwdPortTbForce
ringswitchFwdPortTbForce.description: If this variable is set to enable, transparent forwarding will be enabled, regardless of the spanning tree state machine.

ringswitchFwdPortStpMaster.name: ringswitchFwdPortStpMaster
ringswitchFwdPortStpMaster.description: If this variable is non-zero, it is the interface number of another port, and the spanning tree state machine will be slaved to that port. A port may not be slaved to itself, to any other slaved port, or to a port where transparent bridging is forced (see description of ringswitchFwdPortTbForce).

ringswitchFwdPortSteState.name: ringswitchFwdPortSteState
ringswitchFwdPortSteState.description: The current spanning tree explorer propagation state.

ringswitchFwdPortTbUnicastInFrames.name: ringswitchFwdPortTbUnicastInFrames
ringswitchFwdPortTbUnicastInFrames.description: The number of unicast frames received by this port and transparently forwarded to another port.

ringswitchFwdPortTbUnicastOutFrames.name: ringswitchFwdPortTbUnicastOutFrames
ringswitchFwdPortTbUnicastOutFrames.description: The number of unicast frames transmitted by this port having been transparently forwarded from another port.

ringswitchFwdPortTbBroadcastInFrames.name: ringswitchFwdPortTbBroadcastInFrames
ringswitchFwdPortTbBroadcastInFrames.description: The number of broadcast frames received by this port and transparently forwarded to other ports.

ringswitchFwdPortTbBroadcastOutFrames.name: ringswitchFwdPortTbBroadcastOutFrames
ringswitchFwdPortTbBroadcastOutFrames.description: The number of broadcast frames transmitted by this port having been transparently forwarded from another port.

ringswitchFwdPortTbMulticastInFrames.name: ringswitchFwdPortTbMulticastInFrames
ringswitchFwdPortTbMulticastInFrames.description: The number of multicast frames received by this port and transparently forwarded to other ports.

ringswitchFwdPortTbMulticastOutFrames.name: ringswitchFwdPortTbMulticastOutFrames
ringswitchFwdPortTbMulticastOutFrames.description: The number of multicast frames transmitted by this port having been transparently forwarded from another port.

ringswitchFwdPortTbMiscInFrames.name: ringswitchFwdPortTbMiscInFrames
ringswitchFwdPortTbMiscInFrames.description: The number of unicast frames received by this port and transparently forwarded (flooded) to other ports.

ringswitchFwdPortTbMiscOutFrames.name: ringswitchFwdPortTbMiscOutFrames
ringswitchFwdPortTbMiscOutFrames.description: The number of unicast frames transmitted by this port having been transparently forwarded (flooded) from another port.

ringswitchFwdPortMatrixSrSpecFrames.name: ringswitchFwdPortMatrixSrSpecFrames
ringswitchFwdPortMatrixSrSpecFrames.description: This string contains a count of the specifically routed frames that have been switched from port ringswitchFwdPortNum to each of the possible ports on the ringswitch. The string contains one four byte entry (MSB first) per port.

ringswitchFwdPortMatrixTbUniFrames.name: ringswitchFwdPortMatrixTbUniFrames
ringswitchFwdPortMatrixTbUniFrames.description: This string contains a count of the transparent unicast frames that have been switched from port ringswitchFwdPortNum to each of the possible ports on the ringswitch. The string contains one four byte entry (MSB first) per port.

ringswitchFwdPortEthernetSRBlk.name: ringswitchFwdPortEthernetSRBlk
ringswitchFwdPortEthernetSRBlk.description: If this variable is enabled, on an Ethernet LEC port, then the switch will treat any SR frame (STE, ARE or SRF) going to or from this port as an STE for the purposes of deciding whether to forward it or block it. If it is disabled then the normal SR rules apply. It is ignored for non Ethernet-LEC ports.

ringswitchFwdPortAutoPathCost.name: ringswitchFwdPortAutoPathCost
ringswitchFwdPortAutoPathCost.description: If this variable is enabled on a switch running microcode >= R3.3 then the spanning tree cost for this port will be selected automatically.

ringswitchFwdPortBroadcastReflect.name: ringswitchFwdPortBroadcastReflect
ringswitchFwdPortBroadcastReflect.description: If this variable is enabled on a switch running microcode >= v4.08.01 then, on a DTR link, broadcast frames will be reflected back to the node.

ringswitchFwdTotalRxFrames.name: ringswitchFwdTotalRxFrames
ringswitchFwdTotalRxFrames.description: The total number of received frames switched.

ringswitchFwdTotalTxFrames.name: ringswitchFwdTotalTxFrames
ringswitchFwdTotalTxFrames.description: The total number of transmitted frames switched.

ringswitchFwdBridgeNum.name: ringswitchFwdBridgeNum
ringswitchFwdBridgeNum.description: The global bridge number of the Ringswitch.

ringswitchFwdTbForced.name: ringswitchFwdTbForced
ringswitchFwdTbForced.description: An octet string containing the transparent force state of every port on the Ringswitch. See the description of ringswitchFwdPortTbForce for details.

ringswitchFwdStpMasters.name: ringswitchFwdStpMasters
ringswitchFwdStpMasters.description: An octet string containing one octet for each port on the Ringswitch. If an octet is non-zero, it is the interface number of another port, and the spanning tree state machine is slaved to that port. See description of ringswitchFwdPortStpMaster for details.

ringswitchFwdGlobalHopLimit.name: ringswitchFwdGlobalHopLimit
ringswitchFwdGlobalHopLimit.description: The maximum number of source routing hops that the Ringswitch will forward on any port. This limit is applied to all types of source route frame including all routes explorer frames where it modifies the port hop count limits defined by dot1dSrPortHopCount.

ringswitchFwdTotalBadFrames.name: ringswitchFwdTotalBadFrames
ringswitchFwdTotalBadFrames.description: The total number of incoming frames discarded because of some error. This is the sum of the SR bridge error counters and CRC errors.

ringswitchFwdTotalSpecInFrames.name: ringswitchFwdTotalSpecInFrames
ringswitchFwdTotalSpecInFrames.description: This is the sum of the dot1dSrPortSpecInFrames counter.

ringswitchFwdTotalSpecOutFrames.name: ringswitchFwdTotalSpecOutFrames
ringswitchFwdTotalSpecOutFrames.description: This is the sum of the dot1dSrPortSpecOutFrames counter.

ringswitchFwdTotalApeInFrames.name: ringswitchFwdTotalApeInFrames
ringswitchFwdTotalApeInFrames.description: This is the sum of the dot1dSrPortApeInFrames counter.

ringswitchFwdTotalApeOutFrames.name: ringswitchFwdTotalApeOutFrames
ringswitchFwdTotalApeOutFrames.description: This is the sum of the dot1dSrPortApeOutFrames counter.

ringswitchFwdTotalSteInFrames.name: ringswitchFwdTotalSteInFrames
ringswitchFwdTotalSteInFrames.description: This is the sum of the dot1dSrPortSteInFrames counter.

ringswitchFwdTotalSteOutFrames.name: ringswitchFwdTotalSteOutFrames
ringswitchFwdTotalSteOutFrames.description: This is the sum of the dot1dSrPortSteOutFrames counter.

ringswitchFwdTotalTransparentInFrames.name: ringswitchFwdTotalTransparentInFrames
ringswitchFwdTotalTransparentInFrames.description: This is the sum of the TpPortInFrames counter.

ringswitchFwdTotalTransparentOutFrames.name: ringswitchFwdTotalTransparentOutFrames
ringswitchFwdTotalTransparentOutFrames.description: This is the sum of the TpPortOutFrames counter.

ringswitchFwdTotalTpUnicastInFrames.name: ringswitchFwdTotalTpUnicastInFrames
ringswitchFwdTotalTpUnicastInFrames.description: This is the sum of the ringswitchFwdPortTbUnicastInFrames counter.

ringswitchFwdTotalTpUnicastOutFrames.name: ringswitchFwdTotalTpUnicastOutFrames
ringswitchFwdTotalTpUnicastOutFrames.description: This is the sum of the ringswitchFwdPortTbUnicastOutFrames counter.

ringswitchFwdTotalTpBroadcastInFrames.name: ringswitchFwdTotalTpBroadcastInFrames
ringswitchFwdTotalTpBroadcastInFrames.description: This is the sum of the ringswitchFwdPortTbBroadcastInFrames counter.

ringswitchFwdTotalTpBroadcastOutFrames.name: ringswitchFwdTotalTpBroadcastOutFrames
ringswitchFwdTotalTpBroadcastOutFrames.description: This is the sum of the ringswitchFwdPortTbBroadcastOutFrames counter.

ringswitchFwdTotalTpMulticastInFrames.name: ringswitchFwdTotalTpMulticastInFrames
ringswitchFwdTotalTpMulticastInFrames.description: This is the sum of the ringswitchFwdPortTbMulticastInFrames counter.

ringswitchFwdTotalTpMulticastOutFrames.name: ringswitchFwdTotalTpMulticastOutFrames
ringswitchFwdTotalTpMulticastOutFrames.description: This is the sum of the ringswitchFwdPortTbMulticastOutFrames counter.

ringswitchFwdTotalTpMiscInFrames.name: ringswitchFwdTotalTpMiscInFrames
ringswitchFwdTotalTpMiscInFrames.description: This is the sum of the ringswitchFwdPortTbMiscInFrames counter.

ringswitchFwdTotalTpMiscOutFrames.name: ringswitchFwdTotalTpMiscOutFrames
ringswitchFwdTotalTpMiscOutFrames.description: This is the sum of the ringswitchFwdPortTbMiscOutFrames counter.

ringswitchFwdMaxFrameSize.name: ringswitchFwdMaxFrameSize
ringswitchFwdMaxFrameSize.description: Maximum frame size the switch will forward.

ringswitchLCDTotalDisplays.name: ringswitchLCDTotalDisplays
ringswitchLCDTotalDisplays.description: The total number of displays on the Ringswitch.

ringswitchLCDCurrentDisplay.name: ringswitchLCDCurrentDisplay
ringswitchLCDCurrentDisplay.description: The number of the display that the Ringswitch is currently showing.

ringswitchLCDCurrentMsgText.name: ringswitchLCDCurrentMsgText
ringswitchLCDCurrentMsgText.description: The actual lcd message text, including a carriage return after the first line, and a null character after the second line.

ringswitchLCDTable.name: ringswitchLCDTable
ringswitchLCDTable.description: A table that contains all of the lcd messages that could be displayed by the Ringswitch if the user were to flick the paddle switch.

ringswitchLCDTableEntry.name: ringswitchLCDTableEntry
ringswitchLCDTableEntry.description: Arguments and message number details for each LCD entry.

ringswitchLCDNum.name: ringswitchLCDNum
ringswitchLCDNum.description: The lcd number of the lcd for which this entry contains display details.

ringswitchLCDMsgText.name: ringswitchLCDMsgText
ringswitchLCDMsgText.description: The actual lcd message text, including a carriage return after the first line, and a null character after the second line.

ringswitchLCDUp.name: ringswitchLCDUp
ringswitchLCDUp.description: The lcd number of the lcd which would be displayed if the user clicked the paddle up.

ringswitchLCDDown.name: ringswitchLCDDown
ringswitchLCDDown.description: The lcd number of the lcd which would be displayed if the user clicked the paddle down.

ringswitchLANTable.name: ringswitchLANTable
ringswitchLANTable.description: A table that contains virtual LAN information configured into the Ringswitch by the network administrator.

ringswitchLANEntry.name: ringswitchLANEntry
ringswitchLANEntry.description: Name and status information associated with each virtual LAN entry.

ringswitchLANIndex.name: ringswitchLANIndex
ringswitchLANIndex.description: The virtual LAN number for which this entry contains virtual LAN details.

ringswitchLANName.name: ringswitchLANName
ringswitchLANName.description: The name that the administrator has given this virtual LAN.

ringswitchLANPermeable.name: ringswitchLANPermeable
ringswitchLANPermeable.description: In an 'impermeable' group, broadcast frames which were received on a port in the group, but were not originated in the group, are discarded. In a 'permeable' group, such frames are transmitted on the other ports in the group.

ringswitchLANStatus.name: ringswitchLANStatus
ringswitchLANStatus.description: The current status of this virtual LAN, a status of 'invalid' indicates that the virtual LAN's associated name and ring list are meaningless until the group is validated.

ringswitchLANRingTable.name: ringswitchLANRingTable
ringswitchLANRingTable.description: A table that contains the rings associated with a virtual LAN that has been configured into the Ringswitch by the network administrator.

ringswitchLANRingEntry.name: ringswitchLANRingEntry
ringswitchLANRingEntry.description: Name and status information associated with each virtual LAN ring table entry.

ringswitchLANRingGroup.name: ringswitchLANRingGroup
ringswitchLANRingGroup.description: The virtual LAN index for which this entry contains virtual LAN ring details.

ringswitchLANRingIndex.name: ringswitchLANRingIndex
ringswitchLANRingIndex.description: The ring index for which this entry contains virtual LAN ring details.

ringswitchLANRingNum.name: ringswitchLANRingNum
ringswitchLANRingNum.description: The ring number contained in the virtual LAN.

ringswitchLANRingStatus.name: ringswitchLANRingStatus
ringswitchLANRingStatus.description: The current status of this virtual LAN ring entry, a status of 'invalid' indicates that the ring entry is not in use and the associated ring number is meaningless.

ringswitchVirtTBTable.name: ringswitchVirtTBTable
ringswitchVirtTBTable.description: A table that contains virtual LAN information configured into the Ringswitch by the network administrator.

ringswitchVirtTBEntry.name: ringswitchVirtTBEntry
ringswitchVirtTBEntry.description: Name and status information associated with each virtual LAN entry.

ringswitchVirtTBIndex.name: ringswitchVirtTBIndex
ringswitchVirtTBIndex.description: The virtual LAN number for which this entry contains virtual LAN details.

ringswitchVirtTBStatus.name: ringswitchVirtTBStatus
ringswitchVirtTBStatus.description: The current status of this virtual LAN, a status of 'invalid' indicates that the virtual LAN's associated name and ring list are meaningless until the group is validated; see RingswitchRowStatus comments above.

ringswitchVirtTBName.name: ringswitchVirtTBName
ringswitchVirtTBName.description: The name that the administrator has given this virtual LAN.

ringswitchVirtTBType.name: ringswitchVirtTBType
ringswitchVirtTBType.description: The type of this virtual LAN.

ringswitchVirtTBNumArray.name: ringswitchVirtTBNumArray
ringswitchVirtTBNumArray.description: An octet string containing every port number in this virtual LAN, one per octet.

ringswitchVirtTBNumSize.name: ringswitchVirtTBNumSize
ringswitchVirtTBNumSize.description: The number of ports in this virtual LAN.

ringswitchSlotNumSlots.name: ringswitchSlotNumSlots
ringswitchSlotNumSlots.description: The number of slots available in this Ringswitch.

ringswitchSlotTable.name: ringswitchSlotTable
ringswitchSlotTable.description: A table that contains information about each slot in the Ringswitch.

ringswitchSlotIndex.name: ringswitchSlotIndex
ringswitchSlotIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the slot for which this entry contains management information.

ringswitchSlotStatus.name: ringswitchSlotStatus
ringswitchSlotStatus.description: The value of this variable indicates whether or not this slot supports the card that is currently placed in it: invalid - card not supported full-support - card fully supported no-port-open - cannot open ports on card no-port-fwd - cannot forward frames.

ringswitchSlotBasePort.name: ringswitchSlotBasePort
ringswitchSlotBasePort.description: The port number of the first port available in this slot.

ringswitchSlotCardType.name: ringswitchSlotCardType
ringswitchSlotCardType.description: The type of card in this slot.

ringswitchSlotCardId.name: ringswitchSlotCardId
ringswitchSlotCardId.description: The hardware ID number for the card in this slot.

ringswitchSlotCardRevision.name: ringswitchSlotCardRevision
ringswitchSlotCardRevision.description: The hardware revision number for the card in this slot.

ringswitchSlotCardDescription.name: ringswitchSlotCardDescription
ringswitchSlotCardDescription.description: A string containing a textual description for the card.

ringswitchSlotCardNumPorts.name: ringswitchSlotCardNumPorts
ringswitchSlotCardNumPorts.description: The actual number of ports provided by this card when fully configured in this slot.

ringswitchSlotCardLAN.name: ringswitchSlotCardLAN
ringswitchSlotCardLAN.description: The type of LAN supported by the card in this slot.

ringswitchSlotCardLEDs.name: ringswitchSlotCardLEDs
ringswitchSlotCardLEDs.description: An octet string containing the colour of every LED on the card, one per octet: off (1), on-red (2), on-green (3), on-yellow (4), flash-red (5), flash-green (6), flash-yellow (7), flash-blue (8), flash-green-anti-phase (9), flash-yellow-anti-phase (10)

ringswitchSlotIfAdminStatus.name: ringswitchSlotIfAdminStatus
ringswitchSlotIfAdminStatus.description: An octet string containing the ifAdminStatus of every interface on the card, one per octet: up (1), down (2), testing (3)

ringswitchSlotAdapterStatus.name: ringswitchSlotAdapterStatus
ringswitchSlotAdapterStatus.description: An octet string containing the ringswitchGenPortAdapterStatus of every port on the card, one per octet: open (1), closed (2), opening (3)

ringswitchSlotTestError.name: ringswitchSlotTestError
ringswitchSlotTestError.description: An octet string containing the ringswitchFwdPortTestError of every port on the card, one per octet: no-error (1), same-ring (2), duplicate-ring (3), fail-nb (4), bad-rnum (5), fail-b (6)

ringswitchSlotPortHealth.name: ringswitchSlotPortHealth
ringswitchSlotPortHealth.description: An octet string containing the health of every port on the card, one per octet: normal (1), warning (2), degraded (3), critical (4)

ringswitchSlotLastStatus.name: ringswitchSlotLastStatus
ringswitchSlotLastStatus.description: An enumerated value that records the last important event that occurred during the card's operation. This is used in sending traps when such events occur.

ringswitchSlotPortCreated.name: ringswitchSlotPortCreated
ringswitchSlotPortCreated.description: An octet string containing the ringswitchGenPortCreate of every possible port on the card, one per octet: active (1), inactive (2)

ringswitchSlotHealth.name: ringswitchSlotHealth
ringswitchSlotHealth.description: Current health of the card in the slot.

ringswitchSlotVersion.name: ringswitchSlotVersion
ringswitchSlotVersion.description: The version of code / hardware associated with the slot.

ringswitchGenPortTable.name: ringswitchGenPortTable
ringswitchGenPortTable.description: A table that contains information applicable to all ports.

ringswitchGenPortNum.name: ringswitchGenPortNum
ringswitchGenPortNum.description: The port number of the port for which this entry contains Ringswitch management information.

ringswitchGenPortAdapterStatus.name: ringswitchGenPortAdapterStatus
ringswitchGenPortAdapterStatus.description: The status of the adapter used by this port.

ringswitchGenPortAddress.name: ringswitchGenPortAddress
ringswitchGenPortAddress.description: The hard wired address of the port.

ringswitchGenPortLAA.name: ringswitchGenPortLAA
ringswitchGenPortLAA.description: The locally administered address of the port.

ringswitchGenPortInOctets.name: ringswitchGenPortInOctets
ringswitchGenPortInOctets.description: 48 bit version of the interface MIB counter ifInOctets.

ringswitchGenPortOutOctets.name: ringswitchGenPortOutOctets
ringswitchGenPortOutOctets.description: 48 bit version of the interface MIB counter ifOutOctets.

ringswitchGenPortResetCounters.name: ringswitchGenPortResetCounters
ringswitchGenPortResetCounters.description: Use this variable to reset all the counters on this port, including those in the ringswitchGenPort, dot1dSRPort, ifEntry and fddimib groups.

ringswitchGenPortRMONCapabilities.name: ringswitchGenPortRMONCapabilities
ringswitchGenPortRMONCapabilities.description: A value that indicates the RMON capabilities of the port. The value represents the highest level RMON mode which the port can support. 'disabled' is the lowest level and indicates no RMON capabilities 'snooping' is the highest level and indicates that the port is capable of running in all RMON modes.

ringswitchGenPortRMONMode.name: ringswitchGenPortRMONMode
ringswitchGenPortRMONMode.description: Controls the types of frames passed to the RMON probe function for processing as follows: disabled - no frames passed to the RMON probe economy - MAC frames required for token ring specific groups as follows: MLStats table Token Ring Ring station table standard - all frames snooping - all frames provided by the 'economy' mode plus any frames originating from or destined for the 'snoop address' controlled by ringswitchGenPortRMONSnoop

ringswitchGenPortRMONSnoop.name: ringswitchGenPortRMONSnoop
ringswitchGenPortRMONSnoop.description: This controls the RMON snoop address used when ringswitchGenPortRMONMode is set to 'snooping'. A value of all zeroes results in no snooping taking place.

ringswitchGenPortIPXNet.name: ringswitchGenPortIPXNet
ringswitchGenPortIPXNet.description: The IPX network number of the port.

ringswitchGenPortLastStatus.name: ringswitchGenPortLastStatus
ringswitchGenPortLastStatus.description: An enumerated value that records the last important event that occurred during the port's operation. This is used in sending traps when such events occur.

ringswitchGenPortCreate.name: ringswitchGenPortCreate
ringswitchGenPortCreate.description: This variable is used to dynamically create and destroy Ringswitch ports. When a port is active, all the mib table entries relevant to the type of port will be in existence. When a port is inactive no entry will exist for that port in the ringswitchGenPort table and no other port based mib table entries will exist for that port. To create a port the manager should issue a set request with a value of active which will result in an entry being created in the ringswitchGenPort table and all other port based tables relevant to the port. To destroy a port the manager should issue a set request with a value of inactive which will result in the deletion of the ringswitchGenPort table entry for the port and also the deletion of all other port based table entries associated with the port. Not all types of port can be created and destroyed dynamically.

ringswitchTRIfTable.name: ringswitchTRIfTable
ringswitchTRIfTable.description: This table contains Token Ring interface parameters and state variables not available in dot5Table. There is one entry per 802.5 interface.

ringswitchTRIfEntry.name: ringswitchTRIfEntry
ringswitchTRIfEntry.description: A list of Token Ring status and parameter values for an 802.5 interface.

ringswitchTRIfIndex.name: ringswitchTRIfIndex
ringswitchTRIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the 802.5 interface for which this entry contains management information. The value of this object for a particular interface has the same value as the ifIndex object for the same interface.

ringswitchTRIfRingSpeed.name: ringswitchTRIfRingSpeed
ringswitchTRIfRingSpeed.description: Speed of the ring to which this interface is connected.

ringswitchTRIfRPSEnable.name: ringswitchTRIfRPSEnable
ringswitchTRIfRPSEnable.description: Enables or disables the Ring Parameter Server function on the interface. If this variable is set to enabled, the interface will enable the RPS functional address, and respond to Request Parameters MAC frames, supplying the interface's segment number and soft error report timer value in the response.

ringswitchTRIfRingStatus.name: ringswitchTRIfRingStatus
ringswitchTRIfRingStatus.description: The status of the ring to which this interface is connected. normal: Inserted into Classic ring single: Single Station beaconing: Beaconing Detected normal-fdx: DTR link in full duplex (TXI) mode dtr-wait: DTR Concentrator port waiting for attached station to insert

ringswitchTRIfSoftErrTimer.name: ringswitchTRIfSoftErrTimer
ringswitchTRIfSoftErrTimer.description: Sets the value of the Soft Error Timer Value used by the Ring Parameter Server function on this interface. When this function is enabled it will respond to Request Parameters MAC frames, supplying this value in the response as well as the segment number. Note that this value is in centiseconds.

ringswitchTRIfFrameStatusControl.name: ringswitchTRIfFrameStatusControl
ringswitchTRIfFrameStatusControl.description: Frame Status control is available on Aleutian based hardware. enabled (1); disabled(2).

ringswitchTRIfTokenPriorityControl.name: ringswitchTRIfTokenPriorityControl
ringswitchTRIfTokenPriorityControl.description: Frame Status control is available on Aleutian based hardware. enabled (1); disabled(2).

ringswitchTRIfFastFailoverEnable.name: ringswitchTRIfFastFailoverEnable
ringswitchTRIfFastFailoverEnable.description: Whether the port is a fast failover port. Only ports with odd port number on HSTR cards can be fast failover cards. On other ports this value is ignored. enabled (1); disabled(2).

ringswitchTRIfFastFailoverStandbyStatus.name: ringswitchTRIfFastFailoverStandbyStatus
ringswitchTRIfFastFailoverStandbyStatus.description: The status of the standby port in a fast failover pair. open (1); closed (2); opening (3); ready (4); open-fail(5).

ringswitchTRIfFastFailoverPrimaryPort.name: ringswitchTRIfFastFailoverPrimaryPort
ringswitchTRIfFastFailoverPrimaryPort.description: The primary port in a fast failover pair. unknown (0); left (1); right (2).

ringswitchTRIfFastFailoverTrapInfoReason.name: ringswitchTRIfFastFailoverTrapInfoReason
ringswitchTRIfFastFailoverTrapInfoReason.description: The reason why a fast failover trap was sent. primary-open-fail (1); standby-open-fail (2); links-swapped (3)

ringswitchTRGrpSwtchTable.name: ringswitchTRGrpSwtchTable
ringswitchTRGrpSwtchTable.description: This table contains information relating to group switch rings (each containing five individual ports).

ringswitchTRGrpSwtchEntry.name: ringswitchTRGrpSwtchEntry
ringswitchTRGrpSwtchEntry.description: A list containing Group Switch ring information.

ringswitchTRGrpSwtchIfIndex.name: ringswitchTRGrpSwtchIfIndex
ringswitchTRGrpSwtchIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the 802.5 interface for which this entry contains management information. The value of this object for a particular interface has the same value as the ifIndex object for the same interface.

ringswitchTRGrpSwtchRemoveThreshold.name: ringswitchTRGrpSwtchRemoveThreshold
ringswitchTRGrpSwtchRemoveThreshold.description: The removal threshold, this controls how many times a faulty but persistent node is allowed to attempt to insert into the ring before its port is permanently disabled.

ringswitchTRGrpSwtchRingPollAction.name: ringswitchTRGrpSwtchRingPollAction
ringswitchTRGrpSwtchRingPollAction.description: Defines what happens when the group switch detects a ring poll failure.

ringswitchTRGrpSwtchBeaconThreshold.name: ringswitchTRGrpSwtchBeaconThreshold
ringswitchTRGrpSwtchBeaconThreshold.description: Number of successive beacon frames from one node before a problem is noticed.

ringswitchTRGrpSwtchBeaconAction.name: ringswitchTRGrpSwtchBeaconAction
ringswitchTRGrpSwtchBeaconAction.description: Defines what happens when the group switch detects a succession of beacon frames from the same node.

ringswitchTRGrpSwtchPurgeThreshold.name: ringswitchTRGrpSwtchPurgeThreshold
ringswitchTRGrpSwtchPurgeThreshold.description: Number of successive ring purge frames from one node before a problem is noticed.

ringswitchTRGrpSwtchPurgeAction.name: ringswitchTRGrpSwtchPurgeAction
ringswitchTRGrpSwtchPurgeAction.description: Defines what happens when the group switch detects a succession of ring purge frames from the same node.

ringswitchTRGrpSwtchIsoErrThreshold.name: ringswitchTRGrpSwtchIsoErrThreshold
ringswitchTRGrpSwtchIsoErrThreshold.description: Number of isolating errors before a problem is noticed.

ringswitchTRGrpSwtchIsoErrAction.name: ringswitchTRGrpSwtchIsoErrAction
ringswitchTRGrpSwtchIsoErrAction.description: Defines what happens when the group switch detects too many isolating errors.

ringswitchTRGrpSwtchRingPollThreshold.name: ringswitchTRGrpSwtchRingPollThreshold
ringswitchTRGrpSwtchRingPollThreshold.description: Number of successive ring poll failures caused by one node before a problem is noticed.

ringswitchTRGrpSwtchPortTable.name: ringswitchTRGrpSwtchPortTable
ringswitchTRGrpSwtchPortTable.description: This table contains information relating to individual Group Switch ports.

ringswitchTRGrpSwtchPortEntry.name: ringswitchTRGrpSwtchPortEntry
ringswitchTRGrpSwtchPortEntry.description: A list containing Group Switch port information.

ringswitchTRGrpSwtchPortIfIndex.name: ringswitchTRGrpSwtchPortIfIndex
ringswitchTRGrpSwtchPortIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the 802.5 interface for which this entry contains management information. The value of this object for a particular interface has the same value as the ifIndex object for the same interface.

ringswitchTRGrpSwtchPortAddress.name: ringswitchTRGrpSwtchPortAddress
ringswitchTRGrpSwtchPortAddress.description: Node address of device last inserted in the Group Switch port.

ringswitchTRGrpSwtchSlotTable.name: ringswitchTRGrpSwtchSlotTable
ringswitchTRGrpSwtchSlotTable.description: This table contains information relating to Group Switch cards.

ringswitchTRGrpSwtchSlotEntry.name: ringswitchTRGrpSwtchSlotEntry
ringswitchTRGrpSwtchSlotEntry.description: A list containing Group Switch card information.

ringswitchTRGrpSwtchSlotAdminStatii.name: ringswitchTRGrpSwtchSlotAdminStatii
ringswitchTRGrpSwtchSlotAdminStatii.description: An octet string containing the rptrPortAdminStatus of every Group Switch port on the card, one per octet: enabled(1), disabled(2)

ringswitchTRGrpSwtchSlotAutoPartitions.name: ringswitchTRGrpSwtchSlotAutoPartitions
ringswitchTRGrpSwtchSlotAutoPartitions.description: An octet string with the rptrPortAutoPartitionState of every Group Switch port on the card, one per octet: notAutoPartitioned(1), autoPartitioned(2)

ringswitchTRGrpSwtchSlotOperStatii.name: ringswitchTRGrpSwtchSlotOperStatii
ringswitchTRGrpSwtchSlotOperStatii.description: An octet string containing the rptrPortOperStatus of every Group Switch port on the card, one per octet: operational(1), notOperational(2), notPresent(3)

ringswitchFDDICardTable.name: ringswitchFDDICardTable
ringswitchFDDICardTable.description: A table that contains information about each FDDI card in the Ringswitch.

ringswitchFDDICardEntry.name: ringswitchFDDICardEntry
ringswitchFDDICardEntry.description: A list of FDDI status and parameter values for a FDDI card.

ringswitchFDDICardNum.name: ringswitchFDDICardNum
ringswitchFDDICardNum.description: The slot number of the card for which this entry contains Ringswitch management information.

ringswitchFDDICardSMTIndex.name: ringswitchFDDICardSMTIndex
ringswitchFDDICardSMTIndex.description: This variable takes the same value as the fddimibSMTIndex variable associated with this FDDI card.

ringswitchFDDICardFixupMode.name: ringswitchFDDICardFixupMode
ringswitchFDDICardFixupMode.description: This MIB variable controls operation of protocol fixups on the FDDI linecard. When set to fddi-all, embedded MAC addresses in frames are bit-reversed to convert the frames into native FDDI format

ringswitchFDDICardVRStatus.name: ringswitchFDDICardVRStatus
ringswitchFDDICardVRStatus.description: This variable is used to enable / disable the FDDI virtual ring.

ringswitchFDDICardVRRingNum.name: ringswitchFDDICardVRRingNum
ringswitchFDDICardVRRingNum.description: The ring number of the virtual ring.

ringswitchFDDICardVRBridgeNum.name: ringswitchFDDICardVRBridgeNum
ringswitchFDDICardVRBridgeNum.description: The bridge number of the virtual ring.

ringswitchFDDICardStatus.name: ringswitchFDDICardStatus
ringswitchFDDICardStatus.description: This variable gives the status of the SMT. Each bit (when set) carries the following information: bit 0 (lsb) : ring-inop, bit 1 : mac-unavailable, bit 2 : twisted, bit 3 : i-am-duplicate, bit 4 : he-is-duplicate, bit 5 : bypass-stuck, bit 6 : trace, bit 7 : long-ring-inop Multiple status values can occur simultaneously. If the port is not open then all bits are set to 0.

ringswitchATMCardTable.name: ringswitchATMCardTable
ringswitchATMCardTable.description: A table that contains information about each ATM card in the Ringswitch.

ringswitchATMCardEntry.name: ringswitchATMCardEntry
ringswitchATMCardEntry.description: A list that contains information about each ATM card in the Ringswitch.

ringswitchATMCardNum.name: ringswitchATMCardNum
ringswitchATMCardNum.description: The slot number of the card for which this entry contains Ringswitch management information.

ringswitchATMCardAdminStatus.name: ringswitchATMCardAdminStatus
ringswitchATMCardAdminStatus.description: This variable is a duplicate of the ifAdminStatus of the SONET interface associated with this ATM card. It is used to enable / disable the ATM card.

ringswitchATMCardRemoteUNIVer.name: ringswitchATMCardRemoteUNIVer
ringswitchATMCardRemoteUNIVer.description: The type of signalling supported by the ATM switch at the remote end of this interface.

ringswitchATMCardLECSAddress.name: ringswitchATMCardLECSAddress
ringswitchATMCardLECSAddress.description: The LECS address that a LEC associated with this card will use. If the configured address fails or is set to 0 then the LEC must find the location of the LECS by either: using a defined ILMI procedure to determine the LECS address; using the well-known LECS address; or using the well-known PVC to the LECS. The LEC will try each of these three methods in turn (if configured to use them) until the LECS is located.

ringswitchATMCardLECSIlmi.name: ringswitchATMCardLECSIlmi
ringswitchATMCardLECSIlmi.description: This variable indicates whether or not a LEC can try to determine the LECS address using ILMI.

ringswitchATMCardLECSWka.name: ringswitchATMCardLECSWka
ringswitchATMCardLECSWka.description: This variable indicates whether or not a LEC can use the well-known LECS address to locate the LECS.

ringswitchATMCardLECSPvc.name: ringswitchATMCardLECSPvc
ringswitchATMCardLECSPvc.description: This variable indicates whether or not a LEC can use the well-known PVC to locate the LECS.

ringswitchATMCardActivePort.name: ringswitchATMCardActivePort
ringswitchATMCardActivePort.description: The port that the ATM card is currently using.

ringswitchATMCardILMIStatus.name: ringswitchATMCardILMIStatus
ringswitchATMCardILMIStatus.description: The current state of the ILMI signalling for this card.

ringswitchATMCardSignalStatus.name: ringswitchATMCardSignalStatus
ringswitchATMCardSignalStatus.description: The current state of the ATM signalling for this card.

ringswitchATMCardHardWiredESI.name: ringswitchATMCardHardWiredESI
ringswitchATMCardHardWiredESI.description: The Hard wired ESI (End Station Identifier) for the card.

ringswitchATMCardLocalESI.name: ringswitchATMCardLocalESI
ringswitchATMCardLocalESI.description: The locally administered ESI (End Station Identifier) for the card. When a set request for this variable is accepted the new value will not take effect until the next time the ATM card is rebooted.

ringswitchATMCardPortB.name: ringswitchATMCardPortB
ringswitchATMCardPortB.description: The state of Port B - whether or not an attempt will be made to use Port B in the event of Port A failing.

ringswitchATMCardMode.name: ringswitchATMCardMode
ringswitchATMCardMode.description: The framing mode used by the front-end.

ringswitchATMCardSONETIfIndex.name: ringswitchATMCardSONETIfIndex
ringswitchATMCardSONETIfIndex.description: Each ATM card provides one SONET interface. This variable takes the same value as the ifIndex associated with this SONET interface.

ringswitchATMCardATMIfIndex.name: ringswitchATMCardATMIfIndex
ringswitchATMCardATMIfIndex.description: Each ATM card provides one ATM interface. This variable takes the same value as the ifIndex associated with this ATM interface.

ringswitchATMCardAAL5IfIndex.name: ringswitchATMCardAAL5IfIndex
ringswitchATMCardAAL5IfIndex.description: Each ATM card provides one AAL5 interface. This variable takes the same value as the ifIndex associated with this AAL5 interface.

ringswitchATMCardRowStatuses.name: ringswitchATMCardRowStatuses
ringswitchATMCardRowStatuses.description: An octet string containing the lecRowStatus for each LEC on this ATM card.

ringswitchATMCardMediaType.name: ringswitchATMCardMediaType
ringswitchATMCardMediaType.description: The media type of this ATM card.

ringswitchATMCardConfigUNIVer.name: ringswitchATMCardConfigUNIVer
ringswitchATMCardConfigUNIVer.description: The type of signalling that is configured for the interface.

ringswitchATMCardActualUNIVer.name: ringswitchATMCardActualUNIVer
ringswitchATMCardActualUNIVer.description: The type of signalling that is currently being used on the interface. This may reflect a manually configured value for the signalling type, or may be determined by other means such as auto- configuration.

ringswitchATMCardEthLecSupport.name: ringswitchATMCardEthLecSupport
ringswitchATMCardEthLecSupport.description: Does this ATM card support Ethernet LEC.

ringswitchATMPortTable.name: ringswitchATMPortTable
ringswitchATMPortTable.description: A table that contains information about each LEC in the Ringswitch.

ringswitchATMPortEntry.name: ringswitchATMPortEntry
ringswitchATMPortEntry.description: A list that contains information about each LEC in the Ringswitch.

ringswitchATMPortNum.name: ringswitchATMPortNum
ringswitchATMPortNum.description: The port number of the port for which this entry contains LEC information.

ringswitchATMPortFailReason.name: ringswitchATMPortFailReason
ringswitchATMPortFailReason.description: The reason why this LEC failed to open.

ringswitchATMPortFailSecondary.name: ringswitchATMPortFailSecondary
ringswitchATMPortFailSecondary.description: More information on why this LEC failed to open. Only valid if ringswitchATMFailReason is either config-failed(4) or join-failed(6).

ringswitchATMPortIPXTypeETH.name: ringswitchATMPortIPXTypeETH
ringswitchATMPortIPXTypeETH.description: This variable specifies the encapsulation type on Ethernet for all IPX frames forwarded from onto an Ethernet LEC

ringswitchATMPortIPXTypeTRN.name: ringswitchATMPortIPXTypeTRN
ringswitchATMPortIPXTypeTRN.description: This variable specifies the encapsulation type on TRN for all IPX frames forwarded from an Ethernet LEC

ringswitchATMPortIPXEvenize.name: ringswitchATMPortIPXEvenize
ringswitchATMPortIPXEvenize.description: If this variable is set to enable then all IPX packets forwarded in either direction to be even length by adding a zero padding byte if required

ringswitchATMPortIPXBufLimit.name: ringswitchATMPortIPXBufLimit
ringswitchATMPortIPXBufLimit.description: If this variable is enabled then any NCP buffer size negotiation requests are intercepted and the requested frame size is limit to something less than the ELAN's maximum size

ringswitchATMPortIPXEnable.name: ringswitchATMPortIPXEnable
ringswitchATMPortIPXEnable.description: If this variable is enabled on an Ethernet LEC port then the LEC will do translational bridging of IPX frames, otherwise it will discard them. It is ignored for Token Ring LECs

ringswitchATMPortIPEnable.name: ringswitchATMPortIPEnable
ringswitchATMPortIPEnable.description: If this variable is enabled on an Ethernet LEC port then the LEC will do translational bridging of IP, ARP and RARP frames, otherwise it will discard them. It is ignored for Token Ring LECs

ringswitchATMPortIPMulticastType.name: ringswitchATMPortIPMulticastType
ringswitchATMPortIPMulticastType.description: This variable specifies the type of MAC address to use as the destination for IP multicast frames on Token Ring. It is ignored for Token Ring LECs

ringswitchTLSCardTable.name: ringswitchTLSCardTable
ringswitchTLSCardTable.description: A table that contains information about each TLS card in the Ringswitch.

ringswitchTLSCardEntry.name: ringswitchTLSCardEntry
ringswitchTLSCardEntry.description: A list that contains information about each TLS card in the Ringswitch.

ringswitchTLSCardNum.name: ringswitchTLSCardNum
ringswitchTLSCardNum.description: The slot number of the card for which this entry contains Ringswitch management information.

ringswitchTLSCardRowStatuses.name: ringswitchTLSCardRowStatuses
ringswitchTLSCardRowStatuses.description: An octet string containing the legRowStatus for each LEG on this TLS card.

ringswitchTLSCardRIPTTL.name: ringswitchTLSCardRIPTTL
ringswitchTLSCardRIPTTL.description: An integer giving the value to use for the TTL (Time to Live) field in RIP frames.

ringswitchTLSCardRIPInterval.name: ringswitchTLSCardRIPInterval
ringswitchTLSCardRIPInterval.description: An integer giving the interval in seconds between RIP anouncements.

ringswitchTLSCardRIPAging.name: ringswitchTLSCardRIPAging
ringswitchTLSCardRIPAging.description: Time in seconds to age out routes learnt through RIP.

ringswitchTLSCardDefRoute.name: ringswitchTLSCardDefRoute
ringswitchTLSCardDefRoute.description: The IP address of a gateway to use as the default route.

ringswitchTLSCardDefRouteMetric.name: ringswitchTLSCardDefRouteMetric
ringswitchTLSCardDefRouteMetric.description: The metric to use for the default route.

ringswitchTLSCardRIPFlags.name: ringswitchTLSCardRIPFlags
ringswitchTLSCardRIPFlags.description: RIP flags for the TLS card. Bit 0 is set to indicate Ignore the Neighbours List. Bit 1 is set to indicate that routes learnt through OSPF should be redistributed through RIP.

ringswitchTLSCardOSPFFlags.name: ringswitchTLSCardOSPFFlags
ringswitchTLSCardOSPFFlags.description: OSPF flags for the TLS card. Bit 0 must be set in an autonomous system border router and cleared otherwise. Bit 1 is not currently used. Bit 2 indicates that RIP routes should be exported to OSPF. Bit 3 indicates that static routes should be exported to OSPF. Bit 15 is the master OSPF enable for the card.

ringswitchTLSCardStatsCpuUsage.name: ringswitchTLSCardStatsCpuUsage
ringswitchTLSCardStatsCpuUsage.description: The estimated CPU usage on the TLS card in a second measured in hundredths of a percent.

ringswitchTLSCardStatsFreeMem.name: ringswitchTLSCardStatsFreeMem
ringswitchTLSCardStatsFreeMem.description: The amount of free memory in the heap on the TLS card measured in kilobytes.

ringswitchTLSCardStatsFramesFwd.name: ringswitchTLSCardStatsFramesFwd
ringswitchTLSCardStatsFramesFwd.description: The number of frames forwarded per second by the fast forwarding engine on the TLS card.

ringswitchTLSCardStatsMaxCpuUsage.name: ringswitchTLSCardStatsMaxCpuUsage
ringswitchTLSCardStatsMaxCpuUsage.description: The maximum value recorded for the CPU usage parameter.

ringswitchTLSCardStatsMinFreeMem.name: ringswitchTLSCardStatsMinFreeMem
ringswitchTLSCardStatsMinFreeMem.description: The minimum value recorded for the CPU usage parameter.

ringswitchTLSCardStatsMaxFramesFwd.name: ringswitchTLSCardStatsMaxFramesFwd
ringswitchTLSCardStatsMaxFramesFwd.description: The maximum value recorded for the forwarding parameter.

ringswitchTLSCardStatsResetState.name: ringswitchTLSCardStatsResetState
ringswitchTLSCardStatsResetState.description: Write any value to this to reset the three maximum and minimum values above. Always reads as 1.

ringswitchTLSCardARPFlush.name: ringswitchTLSCardARPFlush
ringswitchTLSCardARPFlush.description: Write any value to this to flush the TLS's ARP cache.

ringswitchTLSCardBootPRASecondsThreshold.name: ringswitchTLSCardBootPRASecondsThreshold
ringswitchTLSCardBootPRASecondsThreshold.description: Length of time, in seconds, since the moment a BootP/DHCP client was booted after which the a clients BootP/DHCP requests will no longer be forwarded. Default value is 86,400.

ringswitchTLSCardBootPRAHopsThreshold.name: ringswitchTLSCardBootPRAHopsThreshold
ringswitchTLSCardBootPRAHopsThreshold.description: A maximum value for the hops field in received BootP/DHCP requests. Default value is 4.

ringswitchTLSPortTable.name: ringswitchTLSPortTable
ringswitchTLSPortTable.description: A table that contains information about each LEG in the Ringswitch.

ringswitchTLSPortEntry.name: ringswitchTLSPortEntry
ringswitchTLSPortEntry.description: A list that contains information about each LEG in the Ringswitch.

ringswitchTLSPortNum.name: ringswitchTLSPortNum
ringswitchTLSPortNum.description: The port number of the port for which this entry contains LEG information.

ringswitchTLSPortName.name: ringswitchTLSPortName
ringswitchTLSPortName.description: The name that the administrator has given this subnet.

ringswitchTLSPortMTU.name: ringswitchTLSPortMTU
ringswitchTLSPortMTU.description: The maximum frame size allowed on this subnet. The value must not exceed the maximum frame size of the switch.

ringswitchTLSPortEnable.name: ringswitchTLSPortEnable
ringswitchTLSPortEnable.description: Enable a port to use it. Disable a port to configure it. A newly created port will be disabled.

ringswitchTLSPortIpAddress.name: ringswitchTLSPortIpAddress
ringswitchTLSPortIpAddress.description: IP Address of the port. Used in conjunction with the IP subnet mask to define the subnet for the port.

ringswitchTLSPortIpSubnetMask.name: ringswitchTLSPortIpSubnetMask
ringswitchTLSPortIpSubnetMask.description: IP subnet mask for the port. Used in conjunction with the port IP address to define the subnet for the port.

ringswitchTLSPortRIPRxType.name: ringswitchTLSPortRIPRxType
ringswitchTLSPortRIPRxType.description: This indicates which version of RIP updates are to be accepted. Note that rip2 and rip1OrRip2 implies reception of multicast packets.

ringswitchTLSPortRIPTxType.name: ringswitchTLSPortRIPTxType
ringswitchTLSPortRIPTxType.description: What the router sends on this interface. ripVersion1 implies sending RIP updates compliant with RFC 1058. rip1Compatible implies broadcasting RIP-2 updates using RFC 1058 route subsumption rules. ripVersion2 implies multicasting RIP-2 updates.

ringswitchTLSPortRIPFlags.name: ringswitchTLSPortRIPFlags
ringswitchTLSPortRIPFlags.description: A bit mask of flags to control RIP operation. By default, all defined bits are set to 1. Bit 0 (LSB) says announce default routes, bit 1 says announce host routes, bit 2 says announce static routes, bit 4 says learn default routes, bit 5 says learn host routes, bit 8 enables route hold-down, bit 9 enables split horizon, bit 10 enables poison reverse, and bit 11 enable route summarising.

ringswitchTLSPortIfArray.name: ringswitchTLSPortIfArray
ringswitchTLSPortIfArray.description: An octet string containing every interface port number in this subnet, one port (1-64) per octet.

ringswitchTLSPortRIP2AuthType.name: ringswitchTLSPortRIP2AuthType
ringswitchTLSPortRIP2AuthType.description: The RIP-v2 authentification type. Valid values are noAuthentication, simplePassword or md5.

ringswitchTLSPortRIP2AuthKey.name: ringswitchTLSPortRIP2AuthKey
ringswitchTLSPortRIP2AuthKey.description: The value to be used as the Authentication Key whenever the corresponding instance of ringswitchTLSPortRIP2AuthTypee has a value other than noAuthentication. If a string shorter than 16 octets is supplied, it will be left- justified and padded to 16 octets, on the right, with nulls (0x00). Reading this object always results in an OCTET STRING of length zero.

ringswitchTLSPortOSPFEnable.name: ringswitchTLSPortOSPFEnable
ringswitchTLSPortOSPFEnable.description: Enable a port to use OSPF.

ringswitchTLSPortOSPFAreaId.name: ringswitchTLSPortOSPFAreaId
ringswitchTLSPortOSPFAreaId.description: OSPF area identifier for the port.

ringswitchTLSPortLegFlags.name: ringswitchTLSPortLegFlags
ringswitchTLSPortLegFlags.description: Bits 1 and 0 Configure how to send IP multicast frames over Token Ring. 00 means use broadcast. 01 means use the functional address C000-0004-0000. 02 means use the Group address as on Ethernet.

ringswitchTLSPortOSPFAuthType.name: ringswitchTLSPortOSPFAuthType
ringswitchTLSPortOSPFAuthType.description: The OSPF authentification type. Valid values are noAuthentication, simplePassword or md5.

ringswitchTLSPortOSPFAuthMD5KeyId.name: ringswitchTLSPortOSPFAuthMD5KeyId
ringswitchTLSPortOSPFAuthMD5KeyId.description: The OSPF MD5 key id. This is a byte value of the MD5 key id. It is ignored if ringswitchTLSPortOSPFAuthType is not md5.

ringswitchTLSPortOSPFAuthKey.name: ringswitchTLSPortOSPFAuthKey
ringswitchTLSPortOSPFAuthKey.description: The value to be used as the Authentication Key whenever the corresponding instance of ringswitchTLSPortOSPFAuthType has a value other than noAuthentication. If a string shorter than 16 octets is supplied, it will be left- justified and padded to 16 octets, on the right, with nulls (0x00). Simple passwords use 8 characters. MD5 passwords use 16 characters. Reading this object always results in an OCTET STRING of length zero.

ringswitchTLSPortOSPFCost.name: ringswitchTLSPortOSPFCost
ringswitchTLSPortOSPFCost.description: The OSPF cost of sending a packet from this interface. Default value is 1. A value of 0 is not allowed.

ringswitchTLSPortOSPFPriority.name: ringswitchTLSPortOSPFPriority
ringswitchTLSPortOSPFPriority.description: The priority of this interface when deciding which interface on the attached network should become the designated router. A value of 0 will prevent the interface from ever becoming the designated router. Default value is 1.

ringswitchTLSPortOSPFHelloInterval.name: ringswitchTLSPortOSPFHelloInterval
ringswitchTLSPortOSPFHelloInterval.description: The length of time in seconds between sending OSPF hello packets from this interface. Default value is 10. A value of 0 is not allowed.

ringswitchTLSPortOSPFDeadInterval.name: ringswitchTLSPortOSPFDeadInterval
ringswitchTLSPortOSPFDeadInterval.description: The length of time in seconds before neighbors declare the router down after ceasing to hear a hello packet. It is recommended that this be set to 4 times the hello interval. Default value is 40. The dead interval must be longer than the hello interval.

ringswitchTLSPortBootPFlags.name: ringswitchTLSPortBootPFlags
ringswitchTLSPortBootPFlags.description: Whether the interface forwards BootP and DHCP requests or not. Default is disabled.

ringswitchTLSStaticRouteTable.name: ringswitchTLSStaticRouteTable
ringswitchTLSStaticRouteTable.description: A table that contains a list of static routes.

ringswitchTLSStaticRouteEntry.name: ringswitchTLSStaticRouteEntry
ringswitchTLSStaticRouteEntry.description: An that contains information about one static route.

ringswitchTLSStaticRouteCardNum.name: ringswitchTLSStaticRouteCardNum
ringswitchTLSStaticRouteCardNum.description: The TLS card number using a static route.

ringswitchTLSStaticRouteIpAddress.name: ringswitchTLSStaticRouteIpAddress
ringswitchTLSStaticRouteIpAddress.description: The IP address of a static route.

ringswitchTLSStaticRouteMask.name: ringswitchTLSStaticRouteMask
ringswitchTLSStaticRouteMask.description: The IP subnet mask to use in a static route.

ringswitchTLSStaticRouteGateway.name: ringswitchTLSStaticRouteGateway
ringswitchTLSStaticRouteGateway.description: The IP address of a gateway to use in a static route. This table is indexed by the TLS card and the IP address of the route.

ringswitchTLSStaticRouteMetric.name: ringswitchTLSStaticRouteMetric
ringswitchTLSStaticRouteMetric.description: The metric to use for a static route. Setting the value to zero will delete the entry. Setting it to a non-zero value will cause the route to be registered, so set this field after the gateway and mask.

ringswitchTLSRIPNeighbourTable.name: ringswitchTLSRIPNeighbourTable
ringswitchTLSRIPNeighbourTable.description: A table that contains a list of static routes.

ringswitchTLSRIPNeighbourEntry.name: ringswitchTLSRIPNeighbourEntry
ringswitchTLSRIPNeighbourEntry.description: An that contains information about one static route.

ringswitchTLSRIPNeighbourCardNum.name: ringswitchTLSRIPNeighbourCardNum
ringswitchTLSRIPNeighbourCardNum.description: The TLS card number using a RIP Neighbour.

ringswitchTLSRIPNeighbourIpAddress.name: ringswitchTLSRIPNeighbourIpAddress
ringswitchTLSRIPNeighbourIpAddress.description: The IP address of a RIP Neighbour.

ringswitchTLSRIPNeighbourEnable.name: ringswitchTLSRIPNeighbourEnable
ringswitchTLSRIPNeighbourEnable.description: Setting to 1 marks the given IP address as a RIP neighbour. Setting to 2 removes the IP address from the list.

ringswitchTLSRIPAdvertTable.name: ringswitchTLSRIPAdvertTable
ringswitchTLSRIPAdvertTable.description: A table that contains a list of addresses to be advertised.

ringswitchTLSRIPAdvertEntry.name: ringswitchTLSRIPAdvertEntry
ringswitchTLSRIPAdvertEntry.description: One entry in the RIP advertisement table.

ringswitchTLSRIPAdvertPortNum.name: ringswitchTLSRIPAdvertPortNum
ringswitchTLSRIPAdvertPortNum.description: TLS leg port number for rejection.

ringswitchTLSRIPAdvertEnable.name: ringswitchTLSRIPAdvertEnable
ringswitchTLSRIPAdvertEnable.description: Setting to 1 marks the given IP address for RIP advertisement. Setting to 2 removes the IP address from the list.

ringswitchTLSRIPRejectTable.name: ringswitchTLSRIPRejectTable
ringswitchTLSRIPRejectTable.description: A table that contains a list of addresses to be rejected.

ringswitchTLSRIPRejectEntry.name: ringswitchTLSRIPRejectEntry
ringswitchTLSRIPRejectEntry.description: One entry in the RIP rejection table.

ringswitchTLSRIPRejectPortNum.name: ringswitchTLSRIPRejectPortNum
ringswitchTLSRIPRejectPortNum.description: TLE leg port number IP address for rejection.

ringswitchTLSRIPRejectEnable.name: ringswitchTLSRIPRejectEnable
ringswitchTLSRIPRejectEnable.description: Setting to 1 marks the given IP address for RIP advertisement. Setting to 2 removes the IP address from the list.

ringswitchTLSOSPFAreaTable.name: ringswitchTLSOSPFAreaTable
ringswitchTLSOSPFAreaTable.description: A table that contains information about each OSPF area for a TLS.

ringswitchTLSOSPFAreaEntry.name: ringswitchTLSOSPFAreaEntry
ringswitchTLSOSPFAreaEntry.description: An entry containing information about one OSPF area.

ringswitchTLSOSPFAreaFlags.name: ringswitchTLSOSPFAreaFlags
ringswitchTLSOSPFAreaFlags.description: OSPF area flags. Bit 0 indicates address range active, Bit 1 indicates advertise address range, and bit 2 indicates external routing capability. Bit 15 is a destroy area flag. Setting this bit will cause the area to be deleted.

ringswitchTLSBootPRAServerTable.name: ringswitchTLSBootPRAServerTable
ringswitchTLSBootPRAServerTable.description: A table containing BootP/DHCP servers that the BootP Relay Agent can forward BootP/DHCP packets to. BootP/DHCP requests will be shared amongst the servers in this table unless the requests specify a particular server name.

ringswitchTLSBootPRAServerEntry.name: ringswitchTLSBootPRAServerEntry
ringswitchTLSBootPRAServerEntry.description: Contains information about the BootP/DHCP server.

ringswitchTLSBootPRAServerCardNum.name: ringswitchTLSBootPRAServerCardNum
ringswitchTLSBootPRAServerCardNum.description: The TLS card number using this BootP/DHCP server.

ringswitchTLSBootPRAServerIpAddress.name: ringswitchTLSBootPRAServerIpAddress
ringswitchTLSBootPRAServerIpAddress.description: The IP address of this BootP/DHCP server.

ringswitchTLSBootPRAServerName.name: ringswitchTLSBootPRAServerName
ringswitchTLSBootPRAServerName.description: The name of the BootP/DHCP server. Clients specifying this name in their BootP/DHCP requests have their request frames sent on to this particular server.

ringswitchTLSBootPRAServerEnable.name: ringswitchTLSBootPRAServerEnable
ringswitchTLSBootPRAServerEnable.description: Setting to 1 adds a BootP Relay Agent server with this port and IP address to the list of BootP Relay Agent servers. Setting to 2 removes this BootP Relay Agent Server from the list.

ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRTable.name: ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRTable
ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRTable.description: A table containing a list of VRRP virtual routers.

ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTREntry.name: ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTREntry
ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTREntry.description: Contains information about the virtual router.

ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRPortNum.name: ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRPortNum
ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRPortNum.description: The TLS leg port that this virtual router is configured to use. There can be a maximum of 1 virtual router per leg port.

ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRIpAddress.name: ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRIpAddress
ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRIpAddress.description: The IP address of this VRRP virtual router. This must be a unique IP address on the same subnet as the leg port that the virtual router has been configured to use.

ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRVRID.name: ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRVRID
ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRVRID.description: The VRRP virtual router ID. Only 1 virtual router with this ID can be used on any single Ringswitch.

ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRMacAddress.name: ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRMacAddress
ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRMacAddress.description: This is the MAC address that the port will use for this VRRP virtual router. It will normally be derived from the virtual router VRID using the formula 00-00-7A-00-80-<bitswapped VRID>.

ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTREnable.name: ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTREnable
ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTREnable.description: Setting to 1 adds a VRRP Virtual Router with this port and IP address to the list of VRRP virtual routers. Setting to 2 removes this virtual router from the list.

ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRAdvertInterval.name: ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRAdvertInterval
ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRAdvertInterval.description: The length of time in seconds between sending VRRP advertisements. Default is 1 second. The value 0 is not allowed.

ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRPriority.name: ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRPriority
ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRPriority.description: Priority value used for electing the master router for a VRRP virtual router. Default value is 100. A value of 255 will force this node to act as the master for this virtual router. A value of 0 will force this node to act as a backup.

ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRAuthType.name: ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRAuthType
ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRAuthType.description: The type of authentication used by VRRP on this port.

ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRAuthKey.name: ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRAuthKey
ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRAuthKey.description: The authentication key to be used if ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRAuthType is set to simple.

ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRAdvertDeadInterval.name: ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRAdvertDeadInterval
ringswitchTLSVRRPVRTRAdvertDeadInterval.description: The length of time in seconds after which if no VRRP advert has been received by the master VRRP router then it will change to backup mode. Default is 4 seconds. The value 0 is not allowed. It is recommended that this value be 4 times the value set as the AdvertInterval.

ringswitchEthernetIfTable.name: ringswitchEthernetIfTable
ringswitchEthernetIfTable.description: This table contains Ethernet interface parameters and state variables applying to each ethernet port, and Ethernet-type interface parameters to configure translational bridging to Token Ring.

ringswitchEthernetIfEntry.name: ringswitchEthernetIfEntry
ringswitchEthernetIfEntry.description: A list of Ethernet status and parameter values for a ethernet interface, plus a list of Ethernet-type interface parameters to configure translational bridging to Token-Ring

ringswitchEthernetIfIndex.name: ringswitchEthernetIfIndex
ringswitchEthernetIfIndex.description: The port number of the Ethernet port for which this entry contains Ethernet information.

ringswitchEthernetIfIPXEthType.name: ringswitchEthernetIfIPXEthType
ringswitchEthernetIfIPXEthType.description: This variable specifies the encapsulation type on the Ethernet card for all forwarded IPX frames from a TRN.

ringswitchEthernetIfOperIPXEthType.name: ringswitchEthernetIfOperIPXEthType
ringswitchEthernetIfOperIPXEthType.description: This variable specifies the actual encapsulation type for all IPX frames forwarded onto Ethernet

ringswitchEthernetIfIPXTRType.name: ringswitchEthernetIfIPXTRType
ringswitchEthernetIfIPXTRType.description: This variable specifies the encapsulation type on TRN for all IPX frames forwarded from an Ethernet port

ringswitchEthernetIfOperIPXTRType.name: ringswitchEthernetIfOperIPXTRType
ringswitchEthernetIfOperIPXTRType.description: This variable specifies the actual encapsulation type for all IPX frames forwarded onto Token Ring

ringswitchEthernetIfIPXEnable.name: ringswitchEthernetIfIPXEnable
ringswitchEthernetIfIPXEnable.description: If this variable is enabled on an Ethernet port then the port will do translational bridging of IPX frames, otherwise it will discard them. It is ignored for Token Ring ports

ringswitchEthernetIfIPEnable.name: ringswitchEthernetIfIPEnable
ringswitchEthernetIfIPEnable.description: If this variable is enabled on an Ethernet port then the port will do translational bridging of IP, ARP and RARP frames, otherwise it will discard them. It is ignored for Token Ring ports

ringswitchEthernetIfAdminSpeed.name: ringswitchEthernetIfAdminSpeed
ringswitchEthernetIfAdminSpeed.description: This variable specifies the speed that the Ethernet port will open at.

ringswitchEthernetIfOperSpeed.name: ringswitchEthernetIfOperSpeed
ringswitchEthernetIfOperSpeed.description: The current operational speed of the network to which this interface is connected.

ringswitchEthernetIfAdminDuplexMode.name: ringswitchEthernetIfAdminDuplexMode
ringswitchEthernetIfAdminDuplexMode.description: This variable specifies the duplex mode of the Ethernet port.

ringswitchEthernetIfOperDuplexMode.name: ringswitchEthernetIfOperDuplexMode
ringswitchEthernetIfOperDuplexMode.description: The current operational mode of this interface.

ringswitchEthernetIfIPMulticastType.name: ringswitchEthernetIfIPMulticastType
ringswitchEthernetIfIPMulticastType.description: This variable specifies the type of MAC address to use as the destination for IP multicast frames on Token Ring

ringswitchEthernetIfCacheClear.name: ringswitchEthernetIfCacheClear
ringswitchEthernetIfCacheClear.description: This variable clears the RIF cache

ringswitchEthernetIfSPTEncaps.name: ringswitchEthernetIfSPTEncaps
ringswitchEthernetIfSPTEncaps.description: This variable specifies whether BPDU's received from Ethernet are encapsulated when forwared onto Token Ring. Encapsulated BPDU's are de-encapsulated when forwarded to Ethernet

ringswitchEthernetIfPriorityTagging.name: ringswitchEthernetIfPriorityTagging
ringswitchEthernetIfPriorityTagging.description: When this variable is enabled, frames onto ethernet ring are priority tagged (using 802.1p) with the token ring priority

ringswitchEthernetIfPriorityTaggingVLANI.name: ringswitchEthernetIfPriorityTaggingVLANId
ringswitchEthernetIfPriorityTaggingVLANI.description: VLAN ID to be used when ringswitchEthernetIfPriorityTagging is enabled.

ringswitchEthernetIfAdminIPXNetwork.name: ringswitchEthernetIfAdminIPXNetwork
ringswitchEthernetIfAdminIPXNetwork.description: The IPX network number of the port. If this is zero then the IPX network number is learned automatically.

ringswitchEthernetIfOperIPXNetwork.name: ringswitchEthernetIfOperIPXNetwork
ringswitchEthernetIfOperIPXNetwork.description: The actual IPX network number of the port.

ringswitchEthernetIfSTPBlockingTrapInfo.name: ringswitchEthernetIfSTPBlockingTrapInfo
ringswitchEthernetIfSTPBlockingTrapInfo.description: Trap set if circulating encapsulated BPDU frames are detected (indicating a 3rd party bridge) which cause the port to go into blocking mode. A trap is also sent if the port becomes unblocked after previously being blocked.

ringswitchEthernetIfAdminFlowCtrl.name: ringswitchEthernetIfAdminFlowCtrl
ringswitchEthernetIfAdminFlowCtrl.description: This variable specifies the flow control abilities that the Gigabit port will use. For 10/100 Ethernet ports this variable will always be not-applicable.

ringswitchEthernetIfOperFlowCtrl.name: ringswitchEthernetIfOperFlowCtrl
ringswitchEthernetIfOperFlowCtrl.description: The current flow control operational mode for the Gigabit interface. For 10/100 Ethernet ports this variable will always be unknown.

ringswitchEthernetIfAutoNegotiate.name: ringswitchEthernetIfAutoNegotiate
ringswitchEthernetIfAutoNegotiate.description: This variable specifies whether the Gigabit interface will auto-negotiate the link properties or whether it will force the link up. For 10/100 Ethernet interfaces this variable will always be not applicable. Auto-negotiation for 10/100 Ethernet is done by setting the speed or duplex mode to auto.

ringswitchEthernetIfMediaType.name: ringswitchEthernetIfMediaType
ringswitchEthernetIfMediaType.description: This variable specifies the media type of the 10/100 Ethernet or Gigabit port.

ringswitchEthernetIfAdminMaxFrameSize.name: ringswitchEthernetIfAdminMaxFrameSize
ringswitchEthernetIfAdminMaxFrameSize.description: The maximum frame size requested for the Ethernet or Gigabit port. For 10/100 Ethernet this value can only be set to 1514. For Gigabit other larger values are supported for jumbo frames. Any changes to this value will not take place until the switch is rebooted. The max size available will be dependent on the switch buffer size - 5K or 18K.
